            <h3>Attributes</h3>
            <p>
                A character is defined by the following attributes:
            </p>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Attribute</td>
                        <td>Description</td>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Strength</td>
                        <td>Determines how much damage is dealt, and inventory capacity.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Dexterity</td>
                        <td>Determines how likely a crit is to occur.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Constitution</td>
                        <td>Determines the number of hitpoints.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Intelligence</td>
                        <td>Determines how much magic damage is dealt.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Wisdom</td>
                        <td>Determines how much mana the player has.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Memory</td>
                        <td>Determines how many skills, and knowledge a player can learn.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <h3>Classes</h3>
            <p>
                The game does not have any classes. A player is also allowed to learn every possible skills.
                Weapons give damage or magic damage, which is increased by strength/intelligence. 
            </p>
            <p>
                This will lead to interesting characters, but also the ability to break a character.
                It should be possible to rebalance the attributes.
            </p>

